Connectivity
============

There are many connectivity options available on the |product| industrial PC. It has 2 x HOST USB Type A connectors 1 x network (RJ45) supporting up to
100 Mbps, and up to 2 x RS232 + 3 x 485 interfaces (one of them is shared with the BT/WiFi module, so please contact Chipsee Technical Support at |email|_ 
if you need another configuration). This device also features two CAN interfaces, and a set of opto-isolated GPIO pins for various purposes.

.. _RS232/485/CAN:

RS232/485/CAN
--------------

The serial connmunication interfaces (RS485, RS482, and CAN) are on a 16 Pin 3.81mm terminal connector *(Figure 7)*. Serial communication on both RS485 and RS422 interfaces
can reach up to 115200 kbps.

.. figure:: /Media/ARM/A7/iMX6UL/IO-Peripheras.png
   :align: center
   :figclass: align-center

   *Figure 3: Relation between serial pins on embedded vs. enclosed version of the A7-70HB-C IPC*

The table below offers more detailed description of every pin and its definition:
  
.. table:: Table 2: Connectivity Section
   :align: center
   :width: 100%

   +----------------------------------------------------------------------+
   | **RS232 / RS485 / CAN Pin Definition:**                              |
   +================+================+====================================+
   | **Pin Number** | **Definition** | **Description**                    |
   +----------------+----------------+------------------------------------+
   | Pin 16         | CAN2_H         | CPU CAN Channel 2 H signal         |
   +----------------+----------------+------------------------------------+
   | Pin 15         | CAN2_L         | CPU CAN Channel 2 L signal         |
   +----------------+----------------+------------------------------------+
   | Pin 14         | CAN1_H         | CPU CAN Channel 1 H signal         |
   +----------------+----------------+------------------------------------+
   | Pin 13         | CAN1_L         | CPU CAN Channel 1 L signal         |
   +----------------+----------------+------------------------------------+
   | Pin 12         | RS485_5-       | CPU UART5, RS485 –(B) signal       |
   +----------------+----------------+------------------------------------+
   | Pin 11         | RS485_5+       | CPU UART5, RS485 +(A) signal       |
   +----------------+----------------+------------------------------------+
   | Pin 10         | RS485_4-       | CPU UART4, RS485 –(B) signal       |
   +----------------+----------------+------------------------------------+
   | Pin 9          | RS485_4+       | CPU UART4, RS485 +(A) signal       |
   +----------------+----------------+------------------------------------+
   | Pin 8          | RS485_3-       | CPU UART3, RS485 –(B) signal       |
   +----------------+----------------+------------------------------------+
   | Pin 7          | RS485_3+       | CPU UART3, RS485 +(A) signal       |
   +----------------+----------------+------------------------------------+
   | Pin 6          | RS232_2_RXD    | CPU UART2, RS232 RXD sigal [#f]_   |
   +----------------+----------------+------------------------------------+
   | Pin 5          | RS232_2_TXD    | CPU UART2, RS232 TXD sgnal [#f]_   |
   +----------------+----------------+------------------------------------+
   | Pin 4          | RS232_1_RXD    | CPU UART1, RS232 RXD signal        |
   +----------------+----------------+------------------------------------+
   | Pin 3          | RS232_1_TXD    | CPU UART1, RS232 TXD signal        |
   +----------------+----------------+------------------------------------+
   | Pin 2          | GND            | System Ground                      |
   +----------------+----------------+------------------------------------+
   | Pin 1          | +5V            | System 5V output, up to 1A         |
   +----------------+----------------+------------------------------------+
     

.. [#f] These lines are redirected to the WiFi/BT module. Please get in touch with the technical support at |email|_ 
   if you need different configuration.
   
.. note:: 
  
   A 120Ω termintation resistors do not come mounted by default with the product.
